<br>
What are the merits of each System what are the bad points.  Lets Get this Hammered Down and Settled no more need to delay it.<br>
<br>
 <p>Maya Shadowdancer<br>


<a href="http://www.elysianofbrell.com">Elysian</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch!</span><br>  Posts: 892<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/22/01 11:54:12 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/fenye.jpg width=92 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG System FFA, FCFS, Reservations.</span><hr size=1> Votes FFA.<br>
<br>
The plane is big.  It's a lot larger than hate or fear.  It CAN support multiple groups.<br>
<br>
For reasons of efficiency, FFA is the better system.  A place that's FFA will be more use than a reserved plane.  Reservations force people not to go &amp; kill mobs.  That leaves them up for longer when they could be killed.  By putting a reservation system in, you're insuring that the mobs get killed less often.<br>
<br>
Look at Hate &amp; Fear right now.  Respawn time is only 12-14 hours, but it's effectively 24 hours, because we only have one raid per day.  Given that some raids don't clear the entire plane, or fail entirely, planar usage on Hate &amp; Fear is probably below 50%.  Yet there's an overcrowding of people that want to raid.  Enough so that 4 separate people can post at 12:00:01 for a Sunday Fear raid.  Given the nature of Fear especially, it should probably remain reservable.  However, Hate is a zone that you can port into, do a portion &amp; leave.  It's much harder to do that in Fear.<br>
<br>
I'm all for making PoG FFA for a while, &amp; seeing how things go.  There's no reason why two separate groups can't go into Growth &amp; kill stuff.  It's a big plane, people CAN cooperate. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="315" height="200"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Uber Gimp</span><br>  Posts: 629<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 12:34:57 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res007bh/BrianPic_copy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG System FFA, FCFS, Reservations.</span><hr size=1> I like being able to take 18 or so people in anytime and have a relaxed raid. I think if someone wanted to do something special like take out tunare it would be a simple enough matter to work that out so that people stayed out of the way while that happened. Honestly, its more like the dreadlands then a real plane, and if it were just an xp zone and no armor dropped there it wouldnt even be an issue, cause there's room for lots of people there.. <br>
<br>
I especially see a lot of people who say there isnt time in their day to run a full 8-10 hour plane raid because they only have 4 or 5 hours of play time. Wouldnt it be nice to have a zone where you can run in with a few groups whenever noone is there and kill for a while. Shrug. leave it fcfs imo.  <p>ICQ#-105127301<BR>
<A HREF="http://sr.amiga.tm/" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Silent Redemption Member" BORDER=0 SRC="http://home1.gte.net/res007bh/ThoricPSD3_copy.gif"></A> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/untikabrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ntika Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 12:45:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG System FFA, FCFS, Reservations.</span><hr size=1> I like the idea of being able to organize a group to go up to PoG and just kill at random myself.  The major issue is that right now we have no form of control on this plane and it has led to chaotic situations with lots of mudslinging.<br>
<br>
The ONLY thing we have right now are INTENTIONS.<br>
<br>
Let's get a system set up for this ASAP and by god, get rid of the intention thread.  It's a dead horse anyway.<br>
<br>
EDIT:  Not the intention thread, meant intention forum. <p>Ntika Ningamouse<BR>
55th Gnomish Rogue<BR>
