<br>
Personally, my opinion is to just keep it FFA, as it is now, and just respect other raids in there.  Keep your party clear of others, and pull at your leisure.<br>
<br>
Is that any different from FCFS as mentioned above?   <p><a href="http://pub32.ezboard.com/benshadowed">
<img src=http://acs.tamu.edu/~jmc6588/eddee2.gif border=0></img></a>
<br>
<img src="http://acs.tamu.edu/~jmc6588/sig2.jpg"></img></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvulgarrdisruptor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vulgarr Disruptor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 9:18:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG System FFA, FCFS, Reservations.</span><hr size=1> I'd have to lean towards Reservation, or at least we continue to post and respect Intentions. It is a huge place, yet it CAN be cleared in one attempt. The bosses will take a massive assault to clear and the respawn time is long enough to screw with people's attempts 3 days later. I'd rather see one well-prepared big raid every 3 days than a sloppy half-assed farming session around the clock. I like big raids and playing/socializing with folks I don't normally see. Scheduling sometimes forces unlikely allies to work together, enableing Brell to accomplish things we otherwise wouldn't if everyone did their own thing and worked against one another. FFA can only lead to more fighting and bitching; the boards are already neck deep in it. The ultimate decision comes down to opening a Growth Schedule forum or a Growth Rants forum. We'll be drowning soon in one or the other.<br>
<br>
V.D.<br>
Ogre Oracle <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvulgarrdisruptor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vulgarr Disruptor</A> at: 1/23/01 9:16:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usyrillian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syrillian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 9:59:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   PoG</span><hr size=1> I vote for FCFS (I assume this means ffa without the ksing, and rude crap that is associated with ffa).  If it has to be another preplanned full raid only zone, it will be another that a lot of people won't get to do because of time constraints <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It's big enough that multiple groups can be in different areas and likely not step on each others toes.... Basically I agree with everything Adun(e) and Thoric have posted.  Just communicate once in the zone, rather than on the boards <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
